# Investing for Beginners: Complete Guide to Start Investing

**By BankDeMark Editorial Team | Updated May 2026**

> **Quick Answer:** To start investing as a beginner, open a tax-advantaged account (TFSA or RRSP in Canada; Roth IRA or 401(k) in the USA), make an initial contribution, and invest in a broad market index fund ETF. Start small, invest consistently, and let compound growth do the work over years and decades.

